Install boto3:

pip install boto3

boto3 is the official AWS SDK for Python. It lets you interact with any AWS service programmatically — S3, EC2, SNS, SQS, Lambda, ASG and more. You create a client for the service and call methods on it. Authentication is handled via IAM roles when running on AWS services like Lambda or EC2 — no hardcoded credentials needed. In our auto remediation Lambda we used boto3 autoscaling client to scale the ASG and SNS client to send email notifications.

Simple meaning:

Without boto3:
  Use AWS Console manually ❌
  Click buttons every time ❌
  Cannot automate ❌

With boto3:
  Write Python code ✅
  Automate everything ✅
  Talk to any AWS service ✅
